<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,582,1291]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,799,823]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Miers" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[328,546,798,822]" class="Malacostraca" family="Upogebiidae" genus="Upogebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="darwinii">
<emphasis box="[328,546,798,822]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Upogebia darwinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has frequently been confused with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ortmann, 1894)" baseAuthorityName="Ortmann" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[981,1342,798,822]" class="Malacostraca" family="Upogebiidae" genus="Upogebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hexaceras">
<emphasis box="[981,1001,799,822]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">U</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1021,1135,798,822]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">hexaceras</emphasis>
(Ortmann, 1894)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Nobili, 1906 a)" baseAuthorityName="Nobili" baseAuthorityYear="1906" class="Malacostraca" family="Upogebiidae" genus="Upogebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="octoceras">
<emphasis box="[1409,1429,799,822]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">U</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,260,835,858]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">octoceras</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nobili, G." box="[278,440,834,858]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="13 - 159" refId="ref51383" refString="Nobili, G. (1906 a) Crustaces decapodes et stomatopodes. In: Mission J. Bonnier et Ch. Perez (Golfe Persique, 1901). Bulletin Scientifique de la France et de la Belgique, 40, 13 - 159, pls. 2 - 7." type="journal article" year="1906">Nobili, 1906a</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Subsequently, their taxonomic position was extensively discussed by several authors (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai, K." box="[208,337,870,894]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 106" refId="ref51877" refString="Sakai, K. (1982) Revision of Upogebiidae (Decapoda, Thalassinidea) in the Indo-West Pacific Region, Researches on Crustacea, Tokyo, (special Number) 1, 1 - 106." type="journal article" year="1982">Sakai 1982</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai, K." box="[349,408,870,894]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 185" refId="ref52015" refString="Sakai, K. (2006) Upogebiidae of the world (Decapoda, Thalassinidea). Crustaceana Monographs, 6, 1 - 185." type="journal article" year="2006">2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nguyen, N." box="[420,577,870,895]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="965 - 985" refId="ref51284" refString="Nguyen, N. (1990) Nine Indo-Pacific species of Upogebia Leach (Crustacea: Thalassinidea: Upogebiidae). Journal of Natural History, 24, 965 - 985." type="journal article" year="1990">Nguyen 1990</bibRefCitation>
). Finally, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai, K." box="[689,834,870,894]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 185" refId="ref52015" refString="Sakai, K. (2006) Upogebiidae of the world (Decapoda, Thalassinidea). Crustaceana Monographs, 6, 1 - 185." type="journal article" year="2006">Sakai (2006)</bibRefCitation>
after examining a huge amount of material including 
<typeStatus box="[151,199,907,931]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">type</typeStatus>
specimens of these three species, and with reference to their variable morphologies and wide distribution ranges, discussed the associated problem in detail (
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai, K." box="[719,954,942,966]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 185" refId="ref52015" refString="Sakai, K. (2006) Upogebiidae of the world (Decapoda, Thalassinidea). Crustaceana Monographs, 6, 1 - 185." type="journal article" year="2006">Sakai 2006:101–114</bibRefCitation>
). He finally came to the result that all three species are the same. Therefore, he suggested that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Nobili" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[715,858,979,1002]" class="Malacostraca" family="Upogebiidae" genus="Upogebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="octoceras">
<emphasis box="[715,735,979,1002]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">U</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[749,858,979,1002]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">octoceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ortmann" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[912,1060,979,1003]" class="Malacostraca" family="Upogebiidae" genus="Upogebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hexaceras">
<emphasis box="[912,932,979,1002]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">U</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[946,1060,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">hexaceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
both were junior synonyms of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Miers" baseAuthorityYear="1884" class="Malacostraca" family="Upogebiidae" genus="Upogebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="darwinii">
<emphasis box="[1409,1429,979,1002]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">U</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,246,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">darwinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Nguyen, N." box="[260,481,1014,1039]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="965 - 985" refId="ref51284" refString="Nguyen, N. (1990) Nine Indo-Pacific species of Upogebia Leach (Crustacea: Thalassinidea: Upogebiidae). Journal of Natural History, 24, 965 - 985." type="journal article" year="1990">Nguyen (1990: 984</bibRefCitation>
, tab. 3) compared these three species regarding some important characters including: 1- Number of rostral spines, 2- Lateral expansions of sixth abdominal segment, 3- Denticulation of posterior border of sixth abdominal segment, 4- Shape of telson, 5- Presence/absence of mesiodistal spine on the palm of the cheliped, 6- Denticulation on the cutting edge of fixed finger. Regarding almost all mentioned characters above, our specimens are closely related to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Nobili" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[636,785,1159,1182]" class="Malacostraca" family="Upogebiidae" genus="Upogebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="octoceras">
<emphasis box="[636,656,1159,1182]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">U</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[676,785,1159,1182]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">octoceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; however, the posterior margin of the sixth abdominal segment is weekly dentate. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ortmann" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[465,698,1195,1219]" class="Malacostraca" family="Upogebiidae" genus="Upogebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hexaceras">
<emphasis box="[465,698,1195,1219]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Upogebia hexaceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nobili, G." box="[844,1012,1194,1218]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="13 - 159" refId="ref51383" refString="Nobili, G. (1906 a) Crustaces decapodes et stomatopodes. In: Mission J. Bonnier et Ch. Perez (Golfe Persique, 1901). Bulletin Scientifique de la France et de la Belgique, 40, 13 - 159, pls. 2 - 7." type="journal article" year="1906">Nobili (1906a)</bibRefCitation>
from the Persian 
<collectingRegion box="[1217,1268,1194,1218]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="Gulf" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Gulf</collectingRegion>
was identified by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nguyen, N." box="[186,414,1230,1255]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="965 - 985" refId="ref51284" refString="Nguyen, N. (1990) Nine Indo-Pacific species of Upogebia Leach (Crustacea: Thalassinidea: Upogebiidae). Journal of Natural History, 24, 965 - 985." type="journal article" year="1990">Nguyen (1990: 981)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Nobili" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[452,596,1231,1254]" class="Malacostraca" family="Upogebiidae" genus="Upogebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="octoceras">
<emphasis box="[452,472,1231,1254]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">U</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[487,596,1231,1254]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">octoceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai, K." box="[611,748,1230,1254]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 106" refId="ref51877" refString="Sakai, K. (1982) Revision of Upogebiidae (Decapoda, Thalassinidea) in the Indo-West Pacific Region, Researches on Crustacea, Tokyo, (special Number) 1, 1 - 106." type="journal article" year="1982">Sakai (1982</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai, K." box="[760,817,1230,1254]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 185" refId="ref52015" refString="Sakai, K. (2006) Upogebiidae of the world (Decapoda, Thalassinidea). Crustaceana Monographs, 6, 1 - 185." type="journal article" year="2006">2006</bibRefCitation>
) identified both species 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ortmann" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[1093,1241,1230,1254]" class="Malacostraca" family="Upogebiidae" genus="Upogebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hexaceras">
<emphasis box="[1093,1113,1231,1254]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">U</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1128,1241,1230,1254]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">hexaceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(White, 1847)" baseAuthorityName="White" baseAuthorityYear="1847" class="Malacostraca" family="Upogebiidae" genus="Upogebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtifrons">
<emphasis box="[1296,1316,1231,1254]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">U</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1331,1436,1230,1254]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">hirtifrons</emphasis>
(White, 1847)
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Miers" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[372,501,1267,1291]" class="Malacostraca" family="Upogebiidae" genus="Upogebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="darwinii">
<emphasis box="[372,392,1267,1290]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">U</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[406,501,1267,1291]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">darwinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. For more detailed taxonomic data see 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai, K." box="[942,1089,1266,1290]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 185" refId="ref52015" refString="Sakai, K. (2006) Upogebiidae of the world (Decapoda, Thalassinidea). Crustaceana Monographs, 6, 1 - 185." type="journal article" year="2006">Sakai (2006)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
